                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client with chronic kidney disease on continuous renal replacement therapy (CRRT) without the use of a hemodialysis machine. The nurse determines that which parameter is most important in ensuring success of this treatment?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nContinuous renal replacement therapy (CRRT) provides continuous ultrafiltration of extracellular fluid and clearance of urinary toxins over a period of 8 to 24 hours; it is used primarily for clients with acute kidney injury (AKI) or critically ill clients with chronic kidney disease (CKD) who cannot tolerate hemodialysis. Water, electrolytes, and other solutes are removed as the client's blood passes through a hemofilter. If CRRT does not require a hemodialysis machine, the client's MAP needs to be maintained above 60 mm Hg, and arterial and venous access sites are necessary. The SBP, DBP, and CVP may be monitored but each of these measures a component of the cardiovascular status rather than the complete cardiac cycle.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Evaluate Outcomes\nCognitive Ability: Evaluating\nContent Area: Complex Care: Emergency Situations/Management\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Renal and Urinary: Acute Kidney Injury/Chronic Kidney Disease\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Evaluation\nPriority Concepts: Clinical Judgment, Perfusion\nStrategies: Strategic Words, Umbrella Option              Test-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic words, most important. Recall that the mean arterial pressure is a measure that takes into account the complete cardiac cycle and is therefore the umbrella option that encompasses all other options.",
                        "id": "fb0c565c7ab241369e3d4c3e2f13a18e",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "032096104d4849d8b128e7207e8e7151",
                                "content": "Administer oxygen to the client."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "376d75c6207146898f165f66b612bb22",
                                "content": "Continue dialysis at a slower rate after checking the lines for air."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "23f3c57696244666b504b1763b443f7c",
                                "content": "Notify the primary health care provider (PHCP) and Rapid Response Team."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "a85fcb4532f348df8b1273c882ff87cd",
                                "content": "Stop dialysis, and turn the client on the left side with head lower than feet."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "99ec8047600349f2a934e220b155d1c4",
                                "content": "Bolus the client with 500 mL of normal saline to break up the air embolus."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "032096104d4849d8b128e7207e8e7151",
                                    "content": "Administer oxygen to the client."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "376d75c6207146898f165f66b612bb22",
                                    "content": "Continue dialysis at a slower rate after checking the lines for air."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
